<ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Boundary_curve.mapping_function"><p>
specifies the role of the <express_ref linkend="External_item_identification_assignment:arm:External_item_identification_assignment_arm.External_item_identification"/> for the <b>Boundary_curve</b>.
The <b>mapping_function</b> maps the  <express_ref linkend="Basic_curve:arm:Basic_curve_arm.Trimmed_curve"/> onto the resultant curve which is the <b>Boundary_curve</b>.
</p><note>
This mechanism ensures that the geometry may be exchanged using this part of ISO 103030 even though the mapping function is an externally defined concept.
</note>
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Boundary_curve.basis_curve">
specifies the role of the <express_ref linkend="Basic_curve:arm:Basic_curve_arm.Trimmed_curve"/> for the 
<b>Boundary_curve</b>.  The <b>basis_curve</b> founds the <b>Boundary_curve</b> in the geometric context of the design.
The <b>basis_curve</b> shall be interpreted to be a complex instance of line and  <express_ref linkend="Basic_curve:arm:Basic_curve_arm.Trimmed_curve"/>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Boundary_curve.wr:WR1"><p>
The <b>basis_curve</b> shall not be a <b>Boundary_curve</b>
</p><note>
This prevents cyclic references.
</note>
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Boundary_curve.wr:WR2">
The <b>Boundary_curve</b> shall not be closed.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Boundary_curve.wr:WR3">
The <b>basis_curve</b> shall not be a <express_ref linkend="Basic_curve:arm:Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve"/>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Boundary_curve.wr:WR4">
The <b>basis_curve</b> shall not be a <express_ref linkend="Basic_curve:arm:Basic_curve_arm.Closed_curve"/>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Boundary_curve.wr:WR5">
The start point of the <b>basis_curve</b> shall be mapped onto the start point of the <b>Boundary_curve</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Boundary_curve.wr:WR6">
The end point of the <b>basis_curve</b> shall be mapped onto the end point of the <b>Boundary_curve</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Boundary_curve.wr:WR7">
The <b>mapping_function</b> shall be one to one and onto from the <b>basis_curve</b> onto the <b>Boundary_curve</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Closed_curve +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Closed_curve">

A <b>Closed_curve</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm.Curve"/> that is traced by a moving point 
that returns to an arbitrary starting <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_point"/>.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Composite_curve +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve">

A <b>Composite_curve</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm.Curve"/> that combines more than one 
 <express_ref linkend="Basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm.Curve"/> into its structure.  The <b>Composite_curve</b> shall be continuous.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve.curve_segment">
specifies the role of the <express_ref linkend="Basic_curve:arm:Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve_segment"/> for the <b>Composite_curve</b>.
There shall be one or more  <express_ref linkend="Basic_curve:arm:Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve_segment"/> for a <b>Composite_curve</b>.
No  <express_ref linkend="Basic_curve:arm:Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve_segment"/> shall be specified more than once as a <b>curve_segment</b> for a particular <b>Composite_curve</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Composite_curve_segment +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve_segment">
A <b>Composite_curve_segment</b> is a segment of a <express_ref linkend="Basic_curve:arm:Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve"/>. A <b>Composite_curve_segment</b> associates Curves with a  <express_ref linkend="Basic_curve:arm:Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve"/> to help compose the  <express_ref linkend="Basic_curve:arm:Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve"/>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve_segment.using_curves">
specifies an inverse relationship that specifies that the existence of the <b>Composite_curve_segment</b> is dependent on the 
existence of the  <express_ref linkend="Basic_curve:arm:Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve"/> that specifies the <b>Composite_curve_segment</b> as its <express_ref linkend="Basic_curve:arm:Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve.curve_segment"/>. There shall be one or more  <express_ref linkend="Basic_curve:arm:Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve"/> for a 
<b>Composite_curve_segment</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve_segment.segment_curve">
specifies the role of the <express_ref linkend="Basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm.Curve"/> for the 
<b>Composite_curve_segment</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Trimmed_curve +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Trimmed_curve">
<p>
A <b>Trimmed_curve</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm.Curve"/> 
that has a defined, finite extent.  The <b>Trimmed_curve</b> 
shall be interpreted as a trimmed curve.
</p>
<note>
The <b>Trimmed_curve</b> is necessary to support the specification of 
precise, metric geometry.
</note>
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Trimmed_curve.end_point">
<p>
specifies a role of the <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_point"/> for the <b>Trimmed_curve</b>.
</p></ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Trimmed_curve.start_point">
<p>
specifies a role of the <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_point"/> for the <b>Trimmed_curve</b>.
</p></ext_description>

