  <ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Measurement_path"> 
A <b>Measurement_path</b>  is  a path, direction, or domain of applicability for a dimension or tolerance. The path is represented by a   <express_ref linkend="Basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm.Curve"/>. A <b>Measurement_path</b>  is a general term whose meaning depends on the context entity which is using it.  <example>A surface may need to be smooth only in one directions. </example>
<example>A dimension of a fillet may be specified by its arc length, which is a measurement path.</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Construction_geometry_arm  Entity: Measurement_path  Attribute: defined_by 
   <express_ref linkend="construction_geometry:arm:Construction_geometry_arm.Measurement_path.defined_by"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Measurement_path.defined_by">
	 the <express_ref linkend="Basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm.Curve"/>
 along which the measurement takes place, or a requirement applies.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Construction_geometry_arm  Entity: Measurement_path  Attribute: defined_in 
   <express_ref linkend="construction_geometry:arm:Construction_geometry_arm.Measurement_path.defined_in"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Measurement_path.defined_in">
	 the <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_coordinate_space"/>

 that identifies the geometric context in which the measurement path is evaluated.
</ext_description>

